        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 8:37AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 837 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Brazos, or 9 miles south of Mineral Wells, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Lipan around 855 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Bennett, Patillo, New
Salem, Millsap, Brazos, Dennis, Tolar, and Brock Junction.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 382 and 396.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
